    </div>

    <form id="gate-form" autocomplete="off" novalidate>
      <input
        id="gate-pass"
        type="password"
        placeholder="Password"
        autocomplete="off"
        autocapitalize="off"
        autocorrect="off"
        spellcheck="false"
        aria-label="Password"
      />
    </form>
  </div>

  <!-- ===================== PAGE 2+ — THE DECK ===================== -->
  <div id="deck" aria-hidden="true">
    <div id="eigenfield-bg" aria-hidden="true"></div>

    <div class="deck-scroll" id="deck-scroll">

      <!-- 00 — TITLE -->
      <section class="slide slide--title">
        <div class="slide-inner">
          <p class="tag">SCRNSVR</p>
          <h1 class="title-h">Welcome to <span class="hl">ScrnSvr</span></h1>
          <p class="lede">Replaces compulsive phone-opening with attention-restoring generative art.</p>
          <p class="byline">Clay Devlin &nbsp;·&nbsp; <a href="mailto:clay@scrnsvr.art">clay@scrnsvr.art</a></p>
          <p class="scroll-hint">scroll ↓</p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- 01 — PROBLEM -->
      <section class="slide">
        <div class="slide-inner">
          <p class="tag">01 / PROBLEM</p>
          <h2 class="slide-h">We don't have a screen problem.<br />We have an <span class="hl">opening</span> problem.</h2>
          <div class="stat-row">
            <div class="stat-big">144<span class="stat-x">×</span></div>
            <p class="stat-cap">times the average person opens their phone every day. Most of it isn't a decision — it's a reflex.</p>
          </div>
          <p class="body">The compulsive reach for the phone is the wedge. Intercept that single moment and you change the entire relationship.</p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- 02 — SOLUTION -->
      <section class="slide">
        <div class="slide-inner slide-inner--wide">
          <p class="tag">02 / SOLUTION</p>
          <h2 class="slide-h">Intercept the reflex. Reward it with <span class="hl">stillness</span>.</h2>
          <div class="frames">
            <figure class="frame">
              <div class="phone">
                <svg viewBox="0 0 120 240" class="phone-art" aria-hidden="true">
                  <rect x="0" y="0" width="120" height="240" rx="20" fill="#0c0f14"/>
                  <path d="M60 70 l30 14 v34 c0 26 -16 42 -30 50 c-14 -8 -30 -24 -30 -50 v-34 z" fill="none" stroke="#fad953" stroke-width="3.5" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
                  <path d="M48 120 l9 10 18 -20" fill="none" stroke="#fad953" stroke-width="3.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
                </svg>
              </div>
              <figcaption><span class="step">1</span> You open a blocked app. ScrnSvr shields it.</figcaption>
            </figure>
            <div class="frame-arrow" aria-hidden="true">→</div>
            <figure class="frame">
              <div class="phone">
                <svg viewBox="0 0 120 240" class="phone-art" aria-hidden="true">
                  <defs>
                    <radialGradient id="g" cx="50%" cy="45%" r="60%">
                      <stop offset="0%" stop-color="#ff6bdc"/>
                      <stop offset="45%" stop-color="#a36bff"/>
                      <stop offset="100%" stop-color="#0c0f14"/>
                    </radialGradient>
                  </defs>
                  <rect x="0" y="0" width="120" height="240" rx="20" fill="url(#g)"/>
                  <g fill="none" stroke="rgba(255,255,255,0.7)" stroke-width="1.3">
                    <circle cx="60" cy="108" r="22"/>
                    <circle cx="60" cy="108" r="38"/>
                    <circle cx="60" cy="108" r="54"/>
                    <ellipse cx="60" cy="108" rx="54" ry="22"/>
                    <ellipse cx="60" cy="108" rx="22" ry="54"/>
                  </g>
                </svg>
              </div>
              <figcaption><span class="step">2</span> A piece of generative art unfolds — never the same twice.</figcaption>
            </figure>
            <div class="frame-arrow" aria-hidden="true">→</div>
            <figure class="frame">
              <div class="phone">
                <svg viewBox="0 0 120 240" class="phone-art" aria-hidden="true">
                  <rect x="0" y="0" width="120" height="240" rx="20" fill="#0c0f14"/>
                  <rect x="18" y="86" width="84" height="68" rx="12" fill="#15191f" stroke="rgba(242,237,226,0.25)" stroke-width="1.5"/>
                  <text x="60" y="116" text-anchor="middle" fill="#f2ede2" font-family="Arial" font-size="11">attention</text>
                  <text x="60" y="130" text-anchor="middle" fill="#f2ede2" font-family="Arial" font-size="11">restored</text>
                  <rect x="34" y="138" width="52" height="13" rx="6.5" fill="#fad953"/>
                </svg>
              </div>
              <figcaption><span class="step">3</span> A break modal lets you continue — or close the loop and walk away.</figcaption>
            </figure>
          </div>
          <p class="body center">Same gesture, new ending. The phone becomes a place attention is returned, not spent.</p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- 03 — WHY NOW -->
      <section class="slide">
        <div class="slide-inner">
          <p class="tag">03 / WHY NOW</p>
          <h2 class="slide-h">The moment and the means have arrived together.</h2>
          <ul class="points">
            <li><strong>The backlash went mainstream.</strong> Screen-time anxiety is no longer fringe — it's a household conversation and a buying motive.</li>
            <li><strong>The gate is rare, and we're through it.</strong> Apple's Family Controls entitlement is granted to almost no one. ScrnSvr has it.</li>
            <li><strong>Incumbents punish; we restore.</strong> Today's tools grayscale your screen or lock you out. ScrnSvr gives attention back instead of taking the phone away.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- 04 — PRODUCT / DEMO -->
      <section class="slide">
        <div class="slide-inner slide-inner--wide">
          <p class="tag">04 / PRODUCT</p>
          <h2 class="slide-h"><span class="hl">TestFlight is live.</span> It's real, and it's running today.</h2>
          <div class="demo-row">
            <div class="qr" aria-hidden="true">
              <svg viewBox="0 0 100 100" width="150" height="150">
                <rect width="100" height="100" fill="#0c0f14"/>
                <g fill="#9be3b0">
                  <rect x="8" y="8" width="22" height="22"/><rect x="14" y="14" width="10" height="10" fill="#0c0f14"/>
                  <rect x="70" y="8" width="22" height="22"/><rect x="76" y="14" width="10" height="10" fill="#0c0f14"/>
                  <rect x="8" y="70" width="22" height="22"/><rect x="14" y="76" width="10" height="10" fill="#0c0f14"/>
                  <rect x="40" y="10" width="6" height="6"/><rect x="52" y="10" width="6" height="6"/><rect x="40" y="22" width="6" height="6"/>
                  <rect x="40" y="40" width="6" height="6"/><rect x="52" y="40" width="6" height="6"/><rect x="64" y="40" width="6" height="6"/><rect x="76" y="40" width="6" height="6"/>
                  <rect x="10" y="40" width="6" height="6"/><rect x="22" y="40" width="6" height="6"/>
                  <rect x="40" y="52" width="6" height="6"/><rect x="64" y="52" width="6" height="6"/><rect x="88" y="52" width="6" height="6"/>
                  <rect x="40" y="64" width="6" height="6"/><rect x="52" y="64" width="6" height="6"/><rect x="76" y="64" width="6" height="6"/>
                  <rect x="52" y="76" width="6" height="6"/><rect x="64" y="76" width="6" height="6"/><rect x="40" y="88" width="6" height="6"/><rect x="76" y="88" width="6" height="6"/><rect x="88" y="88" width="6" height="6"/>
                </g>
              </svg>
            </div>
            <div class="demo-copy">
              <p class="body">Watch a 60-second walkthrough of the shield → art → break loop on a real device.</p>
              <p class="demo-links">
                <a class="cta" href="#" data-edit="demo-video">▶ Watch the demo</a>
                <a class="cta cta--ghost" href="#" data-edit="testflight">Join the TestFlight</a>
              </p>
              <p class="fineprint">Scan the code or follow the links — strongest card a solo founder can show.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- 05 — MARKET -->
      <section class="slide">
        <div class="slide-inner">
          <p class="tag">05 / MARKET</p>
          <h2 class="slide-h">A large, fast-forming market — and everyone in it blocks.</h2>
          <div class="stat-row">
            <div class="stat-big">$10B+</div>
            <p class="stat-cap">digital-wellness &amp; screen-time market, growing double digits as consumers pay to reclaim their attention.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="comp">
            <p class="comp-label">The consumer comp set</p>
            <div class="comp-chips">
              <span>Opal</span><span>one sec</span><span>Brick</span>
            </div>
            <p class="body center"><strong>They block. We restore.</strong> Every incumbent makes the phone worse to use. ScrnSvr makes the moment better.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- 06 — MOAT -->
      <section class="slide">
        <div class="slide-inner">
          <p class="tag">06 / MOAT</p>
          <h2 class="slide-h">Three things competitors can't copy this quarter.</h2>
          <ul class="points">
            <li><strong>The entitlement.</strong> Apple's Family Controls is real gatekeeping. It took a hard, solo approval process to get — and it's the API the whole intervention depends on.</li>
            <li><strong>The science.</strong> Grounded in Attention Restoration Theory and neuroaesthetics, with active relationships to the researchers — not a vibe, a mechanism.</li>
            <li><strong>The art.</strong> Original generative work, never the same twice. Non-commodity content that can't be scraped, cloned, or commoditized.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- 07 — BUSINESS MODEL -->
      <section class="slide">
        <div class="slide-inner">
          <p class="tag">07 / MODEL</p>
          <h2 class="slide-h">Simple subscription. Premium by design.</h2>
          <div class="price-row">
            <div class="price-card">
              <p class="price-amt">$8.99<span>/mo</span></p>
              <p class="price-sub">monthly</p>
            </div>
            <div class="price-card price-card--feature">
              <p class="price-amt">$59.99<span>/yr</span></p>
              <p class="price-sub">annual · best value</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <p class="body center">Recurring revenue from a daily-use habit replacement. A future line — an NFC ritual object that carries your art into the physical world — is upside, not the core.</p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- 08 — TRACTION & ROADMAP -->
      <section class="slide">
        <div class="slide-inner slide-inner--wide">
          <p class="tag">08 / TRACTION &amp; ROADMAP</p>
          <h2 class="slide-h">Shipped, and accelerating.</h2>
          <ol class="timeline">
            <li class="done"><span class="dot"></span><strong>TestFlight live</strong> — full intervention loop running on real devices.</li>
            <li class="done"><span class="dot"></span><strong>Waitlist open</strong> — collecting signups at scrnsvr.art.</li>
            <li class="next"><span class="dot"></span><strong>AIP Summit demo</strong> — live in front of the right rooms.</li>
            <li class="next"><span class="dot"></span><strong>App Store launch — Q3 2026</strong> — public availability.</li>
            <li class="next"><span class="dot"></span><strong>Fellowship applications in flight</strong> — distribution and credibility tailwinds.</li>
          </ol>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- 09 — FOUNDER -->
      <section class="slide">
        <div class="slide-inner">
          <p class="tag">09 / FOUNDER</p>
          <h2 class="slide-h">An artist who can <span class="hl">ship</span>.</h2>
          <p class="founder-name">Clay Devlin</p>
          <ul class="points points--tight">
            <li>Generative art practice since 2022; curation work with LUME and Subjective.</li>
            <li>Took over the codebase and now owns it outright — design, art, and engineering in one hand.</li>
            <li>Shipped through Apple's hardest entitlement process — Family Controls — solo.</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="body center">The rare founder who makes the thing <em>and</em> builds the thing. Taste and execution in the same person.</p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- 10 — THE ASK -->
      <section class="slide">
        <div class="slide-inner">
          <p class="tag">10 / THE ASK</p>
          <h2 class="slide-h">Raising <span class="hl">$750K</span> on an <span class="hl">$8M cap</span> SAFE.</h2>
          <p class="proof">First SAFE already closed at this cap. ✓</p>
          <ul class="points points--tight">
            <li><strong>Launch</strong> — ship to the App Store and convert the waitlist.</li>
            <li><strong>Growth experiments</strong> — find the repeatable acquisition loop.</li>
            <li><strong>Runway</strong> — 18 months to launch, learn, and raise the seed from strength.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- 11 — CLOSING -->
      <section class="slide slide--closing">
        <div class="slide-inner">
          <div class="closing-mark" aria-hidden="true">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 928.18 963.36">
